    {
      "id": "ee10b228b57a90d3e32d9e86ee7d93a2073bf365",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-27 06:44:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 18: Looks good to me, approved\n\nOne question here is what is the effect of setting the OBD_CONNECT_FID flag?  It seems that even 2.1 clients (MDS OSCs and client OSCs and MGCs) connect to the OST with OBD_CONNECT_FID set.\n\nFortunately, it appears that they do nothing with this flag on the OST if it IS set, but the OST cannot depend on this to enable/disable features itself.  This will have to be handled by the MDT to decide that it is connecting to a FID-enabled OST to start requesting a FID sequence and allocating FIDs.  I _think_ this is how the DNE code is implemented, but just wanted to confirm...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 18
    },
    {
      "id": "3de4174e6f53f7f0886d6019805355c9312470dc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-27 17:20:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 18: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 18
    },
    {
      "id": "40e957d58c532053b449751274d7b1fedb2f71e9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-01-28 04:05:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 18:\n\nYes, OSP will check whether the OST support FID by \n\nstatic inline int osp_is_fid_client(struct osp_device *osp)\n{       \n        struct obd_import *imp = osp->opd_obd->u.cli.cl_import;\n        \n        return imp->imp_connect_data.ocd_connect_flags & OBD_CONNECT_FID;\n}       \n\nIf the OST does not support FID, it will go with old protocol.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 18
    },
